<br>
Once casted, you have 30 seconds maximum to unleash as much damage through spells as possible, but, the spells dont hit the target. Instead, your &quot;servant&quot; saves up all this damage, and when you either give an /unleash command, or the 30 seconds is over, the servant adds up all the damage you did from the time the servant was summoned until this point in time, multiplies it by 4, and then unleashes it all for an all or nothing nuke with 0 aggro to the actual wizard. This would in effect be a Manaburn type spell, although VI could make it so all 32k and under mobs are immune to it. It would basically be a Manaburn for the high-hp mobs, while the Manaburn as we know it is more of a Kunark or 32khp mob spell.<br>
<br>
The Harvest AA ability sounds nice.<br>
<br>
The new familiar also sounds very nice, though I hope it doesn't cost 9 points in addition to the original 9 points for Improved Familiar.<br>
<br>
The Xuzl team idea sounds great, but I think it should be upped to 2 extra swords per ability level (making a total of 8 after level 3, since, from my understanding, you start with 2 pets and then you start adding levels), and should last for 60 seconds (make mages last for longer, like 90 seconds). The fact is that Xuzl does very little damage during a short fight, so the time needs to be upgraded to account for this. If the above was done, this ability would become a very useful one. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=9359>Master Feynan Escafon'ea</a> <br>
